The new hand luggage charges apply to bags placed in the upper compartment, so the small bags installed under the seat will always be free.
Frontier said she would pay $25 if the fees were paid in advance and $100 if travelers only paid once at the boarding gate.
Frontier spokesman Kate O’Malley said the $100 was planned to encourage travelers to pay the fees in advance.
